law.text:
The Office of Professional Education Preparation Programs shall coordinate, promote and support activities designed to:
Identify high school students and other individuals from designated underserved areas of the Commonwealth who have indicated an interest in, and demonstrated potential for pursuing professional careers;
Provide special educational opportunities for such students to prepare themselves for admission to, and graduation from, professional schools;
Provide extramural (off-campus) educational opportunities for professional students in rural and other designated underserved areas of the Commonwealth;
Identify currently enrolled professional students, post-graduate trainees and residents who are deemed to have realistic potential for recruitment to practice in underserved areas of the Commonwealth;
Provide for the intensive recruitment of such students and postgraduate trainees for practice in underserved areas;
Provide technical assistance to communities in their professional manpower recruitment efforts.
